<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>NYT &gt; Technology</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/section/technology</link><description>Technology industry news, commentary, and analysis, with reporting on big tech, startups, and internet culture. The New York Times is a hub for conversation about news and ideas.</description><atom:link rel="self" href="https://rss.nytimes.com/services/xml/rss/nyt/Technology.xml" type="application/rss+xml" /><item><title>Data Centers to Add Billions in Power Costs in 13 States</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/14/business/energy-environment/pjm-electricity-prices-data-centers.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/14/business/energy-environment/pjm-electricity-prices-data-centers.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/14/business/energy-environment/pjm-electricity-prices-data-centers.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>A power auction conducted by a giant grid operator is expected to add $6.3 billion in additional charges to consumers and businesses because of electricity needs of data centers.</description><dc:creator>Ivan Penn</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 00:25:48 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Data center</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Electric power</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Price</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US states</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">PJM Interconnection</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Federal Energy Regulatory Commission</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Governors</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Josh Shapiro</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Pennsylvania</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">Mid-Atlantic States (US)</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Federalism</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/14/multimedia/14biz-pjm-rates-sub-vjgq/14biz-pjm-rates-sub-vjgq-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Leah Millis/Reuters</media:credit><media:description>Northern Virginia is home to several data centers, including the Digital Realty Data Center in Ashburn.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>OpenAI Is Showing Kalshi’s World Cup Odds in ChatGPT</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/13/technology/kalshi-openai-chatgpt-world-cup-odds.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/13/technology/kalshi-openai-chatgpt-world-cup-odds.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/13/technology/kalshi-openai-chatgpt-world-cup-odds.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The partnership, a first of its kind for the artificial intelligence company, will use the prediction market’s data to power some search results about the soccer tournament.</description><dc:creator>Mike Isaac</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 03:34:35 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">live-detache